The paper deals with the problem of unfolding polyhedra, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves combinatorial structures of polyhedra, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of limits of unfoldability involves graph theory (cs.GT) and the paper also discusses the properties of open polyhedra, which can be related to topological data analysis (cs.DS) and computational topology (cs.SI).
